    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A project report on automated headlight control system for vehicles</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Raja rathi, Rameez abbas<br />Sushant gurjar</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">automated headlight<br />control system for vehicles</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6141</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Todayâ€™s condition, road transportation is integral part of every activity and
even common person life. Also the development in modern industries has provided
vehicles at cheaper prices making it affordable to most of the population. This has
resulted in increase in traffic on roads and thus increasing the number of accidents and
fatalities on the road. Driving at night is the most dangerous time to drive, no matter
what weather condition is present. It is advised to use High beam as long as possible
during the night driving condition as it provide better visibility, hence is safer. But
high beam causes glaring effect to any oncoming vehicle. A frequent cause of
accidents at nights is the glare caused by oncoming vehicles which momentarily
blinds the driver's vision. It takes three to eight seconds for a person with good
eyesight to recover from the glare, during this time the probability of occurrence of
accident is very high. To avoid this, it is imperative that as the vehicles approach from
opposite directions, the main beams should be switched OFF and the dipped beams
used instead, so that the two vehicles can pass each other safely.
Manual dipping is not being done satisfactorily in India due to a variety of
reasons, which includes sheer physical strain involved in operation of the dipper
switch hundreds of times every night. The other reason includes a general tendency of
paying more attention to steering. Another major cause is 'ego problem', which makes
each one wait till the other person initiates dipping, which may not happen. Thus the
risk of happening of accidents due to glaring is high</td></tr>
